{"text": "1.3.4 Mass and Weight
Mass of a substance is the amount of matter present in it, while weight is the force exerted by gravity on an object.", "fibs": ["Weight"]}
{"text": "The mass of a substance is constant, whereas, its weight may vary from one place to another due to change in gravity.", "fibs": ["mass"]}
{"text": "The mass of a substance can be determined accurately in the laboratory by using an analytical balance (Fig.", "fibs": ["mass"]}
{"text": "The SI unit of mass as given in Table 1.1 is kilogram.", "fibs": ["SI"]}
{"text": "However, its fraction named as gram (1 kg = 1000 g), is used in laboratories due to the smaller amounts of chemicals used in chemical reactions.", "fibs": ["fraction"]}
