Volume is the amont of space occupied by a substance.", "fibs": ["balance"]}
{"text": "It has the units of (length)3.", "fibs": ["length)3"]}
{"text": "So in SI system, volume has units of m3.", "fibs": ["SI"]}
{"text": "But again, in chemistry laboratories, smaller volumes are used.", "fibs": ["chemistry"]}
{"text": "Hence, volume is often denoted in cm3 or dm3 units.", "fibs": ["volume"]}
