{"text": "While limiting the result to the required number of significant figures as done in the above mathematical operation, one has to keep in mind the following points for rounding off the numbers 
1.", "fibs": ["result"]}
{"text": "If the rightmost digit to be removed is more than 5, the preceding number is increased by one.", "fibs": ["rightmost"]}
{"text": "For example, 1.386.", "fibs": ["example"]}
{"text": "If we have to remove 6, we have to round it to 1.39.", "fibs": ["round"]}
{"text": "If the rightmost digit to be removed is less than 5, the preceding number is not changed.", "fibs": ["rightmost"]}
{"text": "For example, 4.334 if 4 is to be removed, then the result is rounded upto 4.33.", "fibs": ["example"]}
{"text": "If the rightmost digit to be removed is 5, then the preceding number is not changed if it is an even number but it is increased by one if it is an odd number.", "fibs": ["rightmost"]}
{"text": "For example, if 6.35 is to be rounded by removing 5, we have to increase 3 to 4 giving 6.4 as the result.", "fibs": ["example"]}
