{"text": "1.9.1	Empirical Formula for Molecular Formula
An empirical formula represents the simplest whole number ratio of various atoms present in a compound, whereas, the molecular formula shows the exact number of different types of atoms present in a molecule of a compound.", "fibs": ["Formula"]}
{"text": "If the mass per cent of various elements present in a compound   is known, its empirical formula can be determined.", "fibs": ["mass"]}
{"text": "Molecular formula can  further be obtained if the molar mass is known.", "fibs": ["formula"]}
{"text": "The following example illustrates this sequence.", "fibs": ["example"]}
