{"text": "Summary
Chemistry, as we understand it today is not a very old discipline.", "fibs": ["today"]}
{"text": "People in ancient India, already had the knowledge of many scientific phenomenon much before the advent of modern science.", "fibs": ["knowledge"]}
{"text": "They applied the knowledge in various walks of life.", "fibs": ["knowledge"]}
{"text": "The study of chemistry is very important as its domain encompasses every sphere of life.", "fibs": ["study"]}
{"text": "Chemists study the properties and structure of substances and the changes undergone by them.", "fibs": ["study"]}
{"text": "All substances contain matter, which can exist in three states – solid, liquid or gas.", "fibs": ["matter"]}
{"text": "The constituent particles are held in different ways in these states of matter and they exhibit their characteristic properties.", "fibs": ["constituent"]}
{"text": "Matter can also be classified into elements, compounds or mixtures.", "fibs": ["Matter"]}
{"text": "An element contains particles of only one type, which may be atoms or molecules.", "fibs": ["element"]}
{"text": "The compounds are formed where atoms of two or more elements combine in a fixed ratio to each other.", "fibs": ["ratio"]}
{"text": "When the properties of a substance are studied, measurement is inherent.", "fibs": ["substance"]}
{"text": "The quantification of properties requires a system of measurement and units in which the quantities are to be expressed.", "fibs": ["quantification"]}
{"text": "Many systems of measurement exist, of which the English and the Metric Systems are widely used.", "fibs": ["measurement"]}
{"text": "The scientific community, however, has agreed to have a uniform and common system throughout the world, which is abbreviated as SI units (International System of Units).", "fibs": ["community"]}
{"text": "Since measurements involve recording of data, which are always associated with a certain amount of uncertainty, the proper handling of data obtained by measuring the quantities is very important.", "fibs": ["recording"]}
{"text": "The measurements of quantities in chemistry are spread over a wide range of 10–31 to 10+23.", "fibs": ["chemistry"]}
{"text": "Hence, a convenient system of expressing the numbers in scientific notation is used.", "fibs": ["system"]}
{"text": "The uncertainty is taken care of by specifying the number of significant figures, in which the observations are reported.", "fibs": ["uncertainty"]}
{"text": "The dimensional analysis helps to express the measured quantities in different systems of units.", "fibs": ["analysis"]}
{"text": "Hence, it is possible to interconvert the results from one system of units to another.", "fibs": ["interconvert"]}
{"text": "The combination of different atoms is governed by basic laws of chemical combination — these being the Law of Conservation of Mass, Law of Definite Proportions, Law of Multiple Proportions, Gay Lussac’s Law of Gaseous Volumes and Avogadro Law.", "fibs": ["combination"]}
{"text": "All these laws led to the Dalton’s atomic theory, which states that atoms are building blocks of matter.", "fibs": ["’"]}
{"text": "The atomic mass of an element is expressed relative to 12C isotope of carbon, which has an exact value of 12u.", "fibs": ["mass"]}
{"text": "Usually, the atomic mass used for an element is the average atomic mass obtained by taking into account the natural abundance of different isotopes of that element.", "fibs": ["mass"]}
{"text": "The molecular mass of a molecule is obtained by taking sum of the atomic masses of different atoms present in a molecule.", "fibs": ["mass"]}
{"text": "The molecular formula can be calculated by determining the mass per cent of different elements present in a compound and its molecular mass.", "fibs": ["formula"]}
{"text": "The number of atoms, molecules or any other particles present in a given system are expressed in the terms of  Avogadro constant (6.022 × 1023).", "fibs": ["number"]}
{"text": "This is known as 1 mol of the respective particles or entities.", "fibs": ["mol"]}
{"text": "Chemical reactions represent the chemical changes undergone by different elements and compounds.", "fibs": ["chemical"]}
{"text": "A balanced chemical equation provides a lot of information.", "fibs": ["chemical"]}
{"text": "The coefficients indicate the molar ratios and the respective number of particles taking part in a particular reaction.", "fibs": ["molar"]}
{"text": "The quantitative study of the reactants required or the products formed is called stoichiometry.", "fibs": ["study"]}
{"text": "Using stoichiometric calculations, the amount of one or more reactant(s) required to produce a particular amount of product can be determined and vice-versa.", "fibs": ["stoichiometric"]}
{"text": "The amount of substance present in a given volume of a solution is expressed in number of ways, e.g., mass per cent, mole fraction, molarity and molality.", "fibs": ["amount"]}
